page.title: 06A WALK TO WISTON MILL
page.content: On a nature walk from Water Lane to Wiston Mill,following the line of the Mill Stream up to Nayland it is possible to see many varieties of wild flowers.Some are hidden so you have to look carefully.This is a list of flowers seen on a day in May on that walk.Red and white dead nettles, camipions and stitchworts,buttercups, celandine's,cranesbill,speedwell, cow and sheeps parsley,horsetail fern, forget_me_knots,honeysuckle,teasles, ground ivy,bluebells,dames violet, charlock,shepherds purse,clover, violets,goose grass,lesser trefoil, cuckoo pint,balm,comfrey,green alkenet,plantan riburort,vertch and daisies.The footpath was bounded by grass for haymaking fields of barley and one of lettuces.Two fields of pasture were occupied by a herd of friesan cows.
